\end_inset

 modeled influenza spread using a rudimentary 
\series bold
air transportation network
\series default
 in the United States (NODES by airport).
 (1) the speed of disease propagation is quicker in small cities than in
 big cities.
 Disease is easier to engulf a small city in comparison to a big city.
 The likelihood of an infected individual comming out of a small city is
 greater than that of a large city.
 
\end_layout

